# Commit Message Format

Use **one line only** — no subject/body split, no blank line, no multi-paragraph body.

```bash
# ✅ GOOD
git commit -m "Add ec2-remote-dev skill for repo architecture guidance"

# ❌ BAD — multiple lines or body
git commit -m "Add skill

Document Terraform and bootstrap patterns for future development."
```

Guidelines:

- Imperative mood, concise summary of **why** (not a changelog dump)
- No trailing period
- HEREDOC is fine; keep the message to a single line inside it
